  {
    "client_msg_id": "164c9894-3bef-44f4-9157-7be75cf7397c",
    "type": "message",
    "text": "From what I can tell, the much simpler *Olog*s are sufficient for describing what was done, but if there are choices built into the model, then you may need the much more complex *Poly* model (since it’s essentially combinatorial as you make choices)\nI believe both are great frameworks for making models that embed domain knowledge outside of code in a way that can be graphically viewed and *composed*\nThe math is intense though…",
    "user": "UN57U8V53",
